11// P2PTransportChannel wraps up the state management of the connection between
12// two P2P clients. Clients have candidate ports for connecting, and
13// connections which are combinations of candidates from each end (Alice and
14// Bob each have candidates, one candidate from Alice and one candidate from
15// Bob are used to make a connection, repeat to make many connections).
16//
17// When all of the available connections become invalid (non-writable), we
18// kick off a process of determining more candidates and more connections.
19//
20#ifndef P2P_BASE_P2P_TRANSPORT_CHANNEL_H_
21#define P2P_BASE_P2P_TRANSPORT_CHANNEL_H_

89// Adds the port on which the candidate originated.
90class RemoteCandidate : public Candidate {
91 public:
92 RemoteCandidate(const Candidate& c, PortInterface* origin_port)
93 : Candidate(c), origin_port_(origin_port) {}
94
95 PortInterface* origin_port() { return origin_port_; }
96
97 private:
98 PortInterface* origin_port_;
99};

229 std::string ToString() const {
230 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
231 const std::string RECEIVING_ABBREV[2] = {"_", "R"};
232 const std::string WRITABLE_ABBREV[2] = {"_", "W"};
233 rtc::StringBuilder ss;
234 ss << "Channel[" << transport_name_ << "|" << component_ << "|"
235 << RECEIVING_ABBREV[receiving_] << WRITABLE_ABBREV[writable_] << "]";
236 return ss.Release();
237 }

349 // Returns the latest remote ICE parameters or nullptr if there are no remote
350 // ICE parameters yet.

356 // Returns the remote IceParameters and generation that match |ufrag|
357 // if found, and returns nullptr otherwise.
358 const IceParameters* FindRemoteIceFromUfrag(const std::string& ufrag,
359 uint32_t* generation);
360 // Returns the index of the latest remote ICE parameters, or 0 if no remote
361 // ICE parameters have been received.
362 uint32_t remote_ice_generation() {
363 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
364 return remote_ice_parameters_.empty()
365 ? 0
366 : static_cast<uint32_t>(remote_ice_parameters_.size() - 1);
367 }

382 Candidate SanitizeLocalCandidate(const Candidate& c) const;
383 // Clears the address field of a remote candidate to avoid IP leakage. This is
384 // applicable in the following scenarios:
385 // 1. mDNS candidates are received.
386 // 2. Peer-reflexive remote candidates.

389 // Cast a Connection returned from IceController and verify that it exists.
390 // (P2P owns all Connections, and only gives const pointers to IceController,
391 // see IceControllerInterface).
392 Connection* FromIceController(const Connection* conn) {
393 // Verify that IceController does not return a connection
394 // that we have destroyed.
395 RTC_DCHECK(FindConnection(conn));
396 return const_cast<Connection*>(conn);
397 }
